@adamcrofts58 Agreed. It seems to me that the actual generation of wind and solar is well underway and viable as we speak, pretty much. But what we lack is energy storage (so we can keep the energy when it is available, to use when it isn't) and infrastructure; sending DC long distances isn't efficient, nor is conversion. 
I support a more decentralised approach myself, local smaller plants of various kinds according to the local resources, including nuclear, and I think storage solutions are on the way.
But yes, time will tell.
